Description: hp-FEM multiphysics application based on Hermes2D library
 Agros2D is a multiplatform C++ application for the solution of two-dimensional 
 problems described by partial differential equations (PDE), based on the Hermes2D library. 
 The user can create models, solve them using adaptive higher-order finite 
 element methods (hp-FEM), and visualize and postprocess the results.
 Currently, the following problem types can be solved:
  - Electrostatic fields
  - Electric current fields
  - Magnetic fields (steady state, harmonic and transient analysis)
  - Heat transfer (steady state and transient analysis) 
  - Structrural mechanics
